eu.wauz.wauzcore.menu.social

Class TabardBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.wauz.wauzcore.menu.social.TabardBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    WauzInventory

    public class TabardBuilder
extends java.lang.Object
implements WauzInventory
    An inventory that can be used as menu or for other custom interaction mechanics. This inventory lets a player create a tabard / banner for their guild.
    Author:
    Wauzmons
    See Also:
    TabardMenu

      • selectMenuPoint

        public void selectMenuPoint(org.bukkit.event.inventory.InventoryClickEvent event)
        Checks if an event in this inventory was triggered by a player click. Cancels the event and opens the selected view or executes the editing action. Possible actions are determined through the view name. From the overview a new layer can be added, the base color can be changed, or the tabard can be saved or declined. From the base color selection, the new color can be directly loaded into the tabard. From the layer color selection, the layer pattern selection can be viewed with the selected color. From the layer pattern selection, the colored layer can be directly added to the tabard.
        Specified by:
        selectMenuPoint in interface WauzInventory
        Parameters:
        event - The inventory click event.
        See Also:
        open(Player, TabardBuilder), openColorSelection(Player), openPatternSelection(Player, DyeColor), GuildConfigurator.setGuildTabard(String, ItemStack), GuildOverviewMenu.open(Player)
